    <item>
      <title>“Burnout amongst health care workers, especially in the ICU...</title>
      <link>https://www.facebook.com/LeslieforColorado/posts/3574188655966009</link>
      <description></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="https://www.facebook.com/LeslieforColorado/"><img src="https://scontent.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-1/cp0/p50x50/46110182_2103163249735231_8400532839258390528_n.jpg?_nc_cat=110&_nc_sid=dbb9e7&_nc_ohc=pcI0YVaINTYAX__IAaw&_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-1.fna&_nc_tp=27&oh=8b4f40cc02eeabc19e76fb9c167a11d6&oe=5FA8B611" alt="" /></a><a href="https://www.facebook.com/LeslieforColorado/">Representative Leslie Herod<a href="https://www.facebook.com/LeslieforColorado/"></a></a><a href="https://www.facebook.com/LeslieforColorado/posts/3574188655966009"></a><a href="https://www.facebook.com"><i></i></a><p>“Burnout amongst health care workers, especially in the ICU pre-pandemic was at epidemic proportions already,” Anuj Mehta, a pulmonologist at National Jewish Health, told the station. “And it's only worse now. It's going to be a reckoning that we all have to face.”</p><p> The University of Colorado is now using federal grants to provide free mental health assistance for medical employees, including through support groups, individual counseling and a multipart series on resiliency.”</p><p> <a href="https://www.facebook.com/coloradopolitics/">Colorado Politics</a></p><a href="https://www.coloradopolitics.com/coronavirus/report-pandemic-contributing-to-burnout-among-healthcare-workers/article_b96f2af2-0c8e-11eb-a471-2718838a5036.html">Healthcare workers in Colorado and elsewhere are warning about increased levels of stress, anxiety and burnout due to the COVID-19 pandemic, CPR reports.<img src="https://external.fapa1-2.fna.fbcdn.net/safe_image.php?d=AQAaMhz6SVVb2Ntr&w=540&h=282&url=https%3A%2F%2Fbloximages.newyork1.vip.townnews.com%2Fcoloradopolitics.com%2Fcontent%2Ftncms%2Fassets%2Fv3%2Feditorial%2Fa%2Fde%2Fade6b348-4ae1-527d-9a65-9ab11379b50c%2F5e9da4bf4f316.image.jpg%3Fresize%3D890%252C630&cfs=1&upscale=1&fallback=news_d_placeholder_publisher&_nc_cb=1&_nc_hash=AQAJOJ9gklynEAKB" alt="" width="500" height="262" caption="" /></a><p>coloradopolitics.com</p><p>Report: Pandemic contributing to burnout among healthcare workers</p>Healthcare workers in Colorado and elsewhere are warning about increased levels of stress, anxiety and burnout due to the COVID-19 pandemic, CPR reports.<a href="https://www.coloradopolitics.com/coronavirus/report-pandemic-contributing-to-burnout-among-healthcare-workers/article_b96f2af2-0c8e-11eb-a471-2718838a5036.html">Healthcare workers in Colorado and elsewhere are warning about increased levels of stress, anxiety and burnout due to the COVID-19 pandemic, CPR reports.</a>]]></content:encoded>
