      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="https://www.facebook.com/LeslieforColorado/"><img src="https://scontent.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-1/cp0/p50x50/46110182_2103163249735231_8400532839258390528_n.jpg?_nc_cat=110&_nc_sid=dbb9e7&_nc_ohc=pcI0YVaINTYAX__IAaw&_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-1.fna&_nc_tp=27&oh=8b4f40cc02eeabc19e76fb9c167a11d6&oe=5FA8B611" alt="" /></a><a href="https://www.facebook.com/LeslieforColorado/">Representative Leslie Herod<a href="https://www.facebook.com/LeslieforColorado/"></a></a><a href="https://www.facebook.com/LeslieforColorado/posts/3564792223572319"></a><a href="https://www.facebook.com"><i></i></a><p>“In short: The signatures required on the outside of the envelope used to return your mail ballot confirm that the right voter filled out the ballot. They’re matched most often by a bipartisan team of two election judges, and if there’s a problem, the voter has a chance to fix it.”</p><p> <a href="https://www.facebook.com/TheColoradoSun/">The Colorado Sun</a></p><a href="https://coloradosun.com/2020/10/09/colorado-ballot-signature-questions/">Colorado election officials begin mailing ballots to registered active voters Friday. To verify them, election officials check the signature on the envelope.<img src="https://external.fapa1-2.fna.fbcdn.net/safe_image.php?d=AQBZsUDWMFQ3KoTc&w=540&h=282&url=https%3A%2F%2Fcoloradosun.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F15%2F2020%2F10%2FDENVER-ELECTIONS-TRAINING-KS-10072020208.jpg%3Fresize%3D1200%2C630&cfs=1&upscale=1&fallback=news_d_placeholder_publisher&_nc_cb=1&_nc_hash=AQD2uba0rl6jPf7K" alt="" width="500" height="262" caption="" /></a><p>coloradosun.com</p><p>Colorado election officials must verify a voter’s signature to count a ballot. Here’s how it works.</p>Colorado election officials begin mailing ballots to registered active voters Friday. To verify them, election officials check the signature on the envelope.<a href="https://coloradosun.com/2020/10/09/colorado-ballot-signature-questions/">Colorado election officials begin mailing ballots to registered active voters Friday. To verify them, election officials check the signature on the envelope.</a><a href="https://www.facebook.com/votinginformationcenter/"><img src="https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/rsrc.php/v3/yw/r/uboafmf-0hy.png" alt="" width="24" height="24" />Visit the Voting Information Center for official election resources and local updates. Get Voting Information</a>]]></content:encoded>
